About the Speaker: Min-Yen Kan (BS;MS;PhD Columbia University) is an associate professor at the National University of Singapore. He is a senior member of the ACM and a member of the IEEE. Currently, he is an associate editor for the journal “Information Retrieval” and is the Editor for the ACL Anthology, the computational linguistics community’s largest archive of published research. His research interests include digital libraries and applied natural language processing. Specific projects include work in the areas of scientific discourse analysis, full-text literature mining, machine translation and applied text summarization. More information about him and his group can be found at the WING homepage: http://wing.comp.nus.edu.sg/.